5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 276, L.D. 422, “An Act to Require the
10 State to Obtain Municipal Approval Before Placing Noncitizens in the Municipality”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §3112 by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines 7
12 to 10 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '2. Placement of noncitizens by the State or agents of the State. The State or an
14 agent of the State may not place a noncitizen within a municipality without prior
15 authorization from the municipality. A municipality may designate the number of
16 noncitizens the State or an agent of the State is allowed to place within that municipality,
17 and the State or an agent of the State may not exceed the number of noncitizens designated
18 by the municipality.'
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, provides that the
2233 prohibition in the bill on actions by the State also applies to an agent of the State.
